The High Court in Makhanda has ordered the Eastern Cape Education Department to deliver textbooks and stationery to all public schools in the province by month-end. The department had previously indicated that they would only deliver textbooks by the end of April, due to unprecedented budgeting shortfalls. #eNCA speaks to Cameron McConnachie an Attorney from the Legal Resource Centre. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The High Court in Makhanda has ordered the Eastern Cape Education Department to get its act together and deliver stationery to all schools by the end of March. This was after the Department blamed budget constraints for the delays. READ:Â School supplies issue in Eastern Cape The Legal Resource Centre says there is no justification for budget cuts as they have delivered stationery successfully in the previous years. Watch the video above for more details on this story.